                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>P<hi rend="sup">h</hi>
                                                  Cabello</placeName>
                                        <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> December 1852</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqre</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>371 Walnut St. Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">A couple of months ago, being in
                                                  <placeName>Caracao</placeName>, I was
                                        presented<lb/> with the accompanying prospectus, by
                                                  <persName>Samuel Piso, Esqr</persName>, of<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Barcelona</placeName>, and wishing to become a
                                        subscriber to the “Occident<lb/> and American Jewish
                                        Advocate” (Monthly Periodical) I have<lb/> taken the liberty
                                        of filling up my name etc. in the said prospectus<lb/> and
                                        of addressing you on the subject. I am very wishful to
                                        be<lb/> in the possession of the 9 volumes, which have
                                        already appeared<lb/> and the one which is now in progress
                                        of this periodical, and you<lb/> will therefore extremely
                                        oblige me by handing the same to <persName>Captn.<lb/>
                                                  Wilkins</persName> of the Barque Paez, who will
                                        give you $20.—that is<lb/> till the completion of the 10<hi
                                                  rend="sup">th</hi> volume Ulto. <date>March
                                                  1853</date>, and<lb/> also to let me know what two
                                        copies of the new translation of<lb/> the Holy Scriptures,
                                        and one of the <sic>portuguese</sic> form of prayer<lb/>
                                        bound as noted in their respective subscriptions will
                                        amount<lb/> to, so that I may be able to forward you a bill
                                        for the costs fur<lb/> „ther you oblige me by sending the
                                        same, when ready to my ad<lb/> „dress, and by the beginning
                                        of the 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi> volume of the monthly<lb/>
                                        to forward me the numbers as they are issued by the Dallett
                                        pack<lb/> „et, for which I shall remit the subscription in
                                        due time.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Please be so kind as to inform me also, what may
                                        be<lb/> the cost of a Hebrew grammar, in English, Lexicon,
                                        and English<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">&amp; Hebrew</hi></p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>&amp; Hebrew, and Hebrew &amp; English Dictionary, neatly
                                        bound-</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">In return I shall be very happy, in case I can be
                                        of use<lb/> to you, to offer you my services, and remain,
                                        Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(11)">Yours very truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(11)">
                                        <persName role="author">A Myerston</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>371 Walnut <sic>street</sic></placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
